🧠 🧩 Overall System (Big Picture)

👉 Ye app Next.js pe bana hai
👉 Isme:

Frontend (pages)
Backend (API routes)
👉 dono ek hi project me hain 😎
🔥 🪜 Step-by-Step Flow
🟢 1. User Home Page open karta hai

👉 URL:

http://localhost:3000/

👉 Kya hota hai?

getServerSideProps()

👉 Ye:

Server pe run hota hai
/api/todos call karta hai
🔵 2. Backend API call hoti hai

👉 File:

/pages/api/todos.js

👉 Ye karta hai:

res.json(todos);

👉 Matlab:

Fake DB se data nikala
Client ko bhej diya
🟡 3. Server HTML ready karta hai

👉 getServerSideProps:

Data le aata hai
Page ko ready karta hai

👉 Browser ko milta hai:

Todo List (already filled)

👉 Isliye fast + SEO friendly 🔥

🟣 4. User kisi Todo pe click karta hai

👉 next/link use hua tha:

<Link href={`/todos/${id}`} />

👉 Navigation hota hai:

/todos/1

👉 Page reload nahi hota ⚡

🔴 5. Dynamic Route open hota hai

👉 File:

/pages/todos/[id].js

👉 Yaha:

context.params.id

👉 Example:

id = 1
🟠 6. Fir se server call hoti hai

👉 getServerSideProps:

API se data fetch
Specific todo nikalta hai

👉 Page ready:

Todo Detail Page
🟤 7. User "Back" button dabata hai
router.push("/")

👉 next/router:

Programmatic navigation
Wapas home page
🟢 8. User "Add Todo" karta hai

👉 Page:

/add

👉 User input deta hai

🔵 9. API call (POST)
fetch("/api/todos", { method: "POST" })

👉 Backend:

todos.push(newTodo);

👉 Data save ho gaya ✅

🟣 10. Redirect
router.push("/")

👉 Wapas home page → updated list